SAEM avec simulation par MCMC

\[\log f(Y, Z ; \theta) = \langle \Phi(\theta) ; S(Y,Z) \rangle - \psi(\theta)\]

Phi <- function(rho2, sigma2, mu, omega2)
  c(- 1/(2*sigma2), -1/(2*rho2), -1/(2*omega2), mu/omega2)

S <- function(eta, phi)
{
  s <- c(sum((Y - get_obs(m, dt, eta = eta, phi = phi) )^2 ), #id = 1
    sum(eta^2),          #id = 2
    apply(phi^2, 2, sum),          #id = 3
    apply(phi  , 2, sum) )         #id = 4

  attr(s, '1') <- 1
  attr(s, '2') <- 2
  attr(s, '3') <- 2 + 1:ncol(phi)
  attr(s, '4') <- 2 +   ncol(phi) + 1:ncol(phi)
  return(s)
}

Metropolis Hastings

#=============================================================================#
loglik.phi <- function(x, eta, Phi)
{
  s <- S(eta,x)
  
  id <- c(attr(s,'1'), attr(s,'3'), attr(s,'4')) #indice de S_1 et S_{3,.} puis S_{4,.}
  sum(Phi[id]*s[id])
}
loglik.eta <- function(x, phi, Phi) 
{ 
  s <- S(x, phi)
  id <- c(attr(s,'1'), attr(s,'2'))
  sum(Phi[id]*s[id])
}
phi.MH <- matrix(rnorm(F.*G, 0, 1), ncol = F.)
phi.MH <- MH_High_Dim(200, phi.MH, transi, loglik.phi, attr(dt, 'eta'), do.call(Phi, param), verbatim = T)
plot(phi.MH)
eta.MH <- MH_High_Dim(100, matrix(rnorm(N, 0, 1), nrow = 1), transi, loglik.eta,  attr(dt, 'phi'), do.call(Phi, param), verbatim = T)
plot(eta.MH)

SAEM

initialisation

# --- Nombre iteration --- #
M <- 1
u <- function(k) ifelse(k<200, 1, 1/(k-199) )

# ---  Initialisation des paramètres --- #

para <- list( rho2 = 1, #sample(1:5, size = 1),
              sigma2 = 1, #sample(1:5, size = 1),
              mu = rep(1, F.),
              omega2 = rep(1, F.) )

para <- param %>% sapply(function(x) x + runif(1))


# --- Initialisation des chaines MC : Z_0 --- #
etagivenY <- 1:M %>% lapply(function(i) rnorm(N, 0,0.1)  %>% matrix(ncol = 1) )
phigivenY <- 1:M %>% lapply(function(i) matrix(rnorm(F.*G, c(6,3,1), 0.1), nrow = F.) %>% t  )

#Fonction de transition du MH
transi <- function(x) rnorm(length(x), x, 0.02)

Boucle

sim <- function(niter, Phih, etagivenY, phigivenY)
{
  M <- length(phigivenY)
  # etagivenY <- 1:M %>% lapply( function(i) 
  #   MH_High_Dim(niter, etagivenY[[i]], transi, loglik.eta, phigivenY[[i]], Phih ))

  phigivenY <- 1:M %>% lapply( function(i)
    MH_High_Dim(niter, phigivenY[[i]], transi, loglik.phi, etagivenY[[i]], Phih ))

  list(eta = etagivenY, phi = phigivenY)
}

maxi <- function(S)
{
  mu <- S[attr(S,'4')]/G # = S[4]
  return( list(rho2 = param$rho2,#S[attr(S,'2')]/N,
               sigma2 = S[attr(S,'1')]/n,
               mu = mu,
               omega2 = param$omega2))#S[attr(S,'3')]/G - mu^2))
  
}

maxi(S(attr(dt, 'eta'), attr(dt, 'phi')))
